83. Develop a PHP script to accept email addresses and validate it. Display the domain name of the email and result of validation.

AMSWER
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Email Validator</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Email Validation</h2>
    <form method="post" action="">
        <label for="email">Enter Email Address:</label>
        <input type="text" name="email" id="email" required>
        <input type="submit" value="Validate">
    </form>
    <?php
    if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") {
        $email = trim($_POST['email']); // Get email from form input and remove whitespace
         // Check if the email is valid
        if (filter_var($email, FILTER_VALIDATE_EMAIL)) {
            // Extract domain from email
            $domain = substr(strrchr($email, "@"), 1); // Get everything after the '@'

            echo "<p style='color:green;'>✅ Valid Email Address</p>";
            echo "<p><strong>Domain:</strong> " . htmlspecialchars($domain) . "</p>";
        } else {
            echo "<p style='color:red;'>❌ Invalid Email Address</p>";
        }
    }
    ?>

</body>
</html>


OUTPUT
Enter Email Address: 
123@gmail.com
Valid Email Address
Domain: gmail.com
